-- Barclays to pay $280 million to settle mortgage bond claims
-- 
-- Thu Apr 24, 2014 04:18PM EDT
-- None



WASHINGTON, April 24 (Reuters) - Barclays Bank PLC <BARC.L> will pay $280 million to Fannie Mae <FNMA.OB> and Freddie Mac <FMCC.OB> to settle claims that it sold them faulty mortgage-backed securities during the housing bubble, a U.S. regulator said on Thursday.   (Reporting By Margaret Chadbourn; Editing by Chris Reese)  ((margaret.chadbourn@thomsonreuters.com)(+1 202 354 5806)(Reuters Messaging: margaret.chadbourn.thomsonreuters.com@reuters.net))  Keywords: USA BARCLAYS/SETTLEMENT

